AZ: Cochise County, Bonnie Blink, Sierra Vista; 
6 May 2012
; S. L. Williamson. Host: 

Rabidosa santrita
(Chamberlin and Ivie)

(
Lycosidae
), adult female. The wasp dragged the paralyzed wolf spider backwards on the ground, dorsal side upward, grasping its right pedipalp with her mandibles (
Williamson 2012
).

TX: Denton County, Lewisville; 
15 May 2018
; R. Thomas. Host: 

Dolomedes tenebrosus
Hentz

(Dark fishing spider) (
Pisauridae
), adult female. The wasp straddled the paralyzed fishing spider as it laid on the ground, dorsal side upward, and examined it with her antennae (
Thomas 2018
).

MEXICO : Oaxaca State , Sierra Mazateca, Municipality of Huautla de Jiménez, Plan Carlota;
15 April 2016
; D. Barrales. Host: Unidentified species ( Ctenidae ), adult female. The wasp dragged the paralyzed wandering spider backwards through vegetation, dorsal side upward, grasping its left pedipalp or chelicera with her mandibles ( Barrales 2016 ).
